# Git Workflow

Full contributor guide: `CONTRIBUTING.md`.

## Branches

- Integrate on `main`.
- Prefer `milestone/<id>-<slug>`, `feature/<slug>`, `fix/<slug>`, or `chore/<slug>`.
- Never force-push `main`.

## Commits

- Imperative subject; Conventional Commits (`feat:`, `fix:`, `docs:`, …) when natural.
- Milestone briefs may mandate an exact commit message — use it verbatim.
- Never commit `.env`, credentials, or private keys.
- Do not use `--no-verify` unless explicitly requested.
- Commit only when the user/milestone asks.

## Staging discipline

- For documentation-only milestones, stage **only** docs/rules/prompts — leave unrelated application WIP unstaged.
- Review `git status` / `git diff` before commit.
- Prefer path-specific `git add` when the working tree contains mixed work.

## Pull requests

- Include summary, test plan, migration impact, and curriculum/architecture notes when relevant.
- CI must be green on pytest + ruff unless an explicit exception is documented.
